<td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Pet questions</span><hr size=1> I'm just about to hit \24th lvl and have some pet questions:<br>
<br>
- the pet stat chart say that all pets at 24th lvl will dual wielt with the aid of weapons.  Is this still the case?  Can they be two of the same weapons, or do they have to be different weapons?<br>
<br>
- My pet will wield an elemental Defender, does it gain an ac bonus from it?<br>
<br>
- If I summon a suit of phantom leather and give it to my pet, will it gain any AC bonus from it?<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uharrije.showPublicProfile?language=EN>harrije</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 211<br> <font color=#333333>(7/9/02 6:48:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1396.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet questions</span><hr size=1> I haven't tested the level 24 pets in quite a while, but I haven't heard anything about them being changed, so yes, your pets should still be able to dual wield with the aid of weapons. Summon a couple of snake fangs (do you have dagger of symbols yet?) and see if it wields them both. There might be an off chance that your lowest level pet summon would be too low to dual wield, in which case you should reclaim and try again. I honestly don't remember that ever being the case with my 24 pets though.<br>
<br>
The type of weapon won't matter, with the rather obvious exception of two-handed weapons. Your pet won't dual wield if it has a two-handed weapon (and from what I've heard, pets no longer wield two-handers, or stop wielding them when they get the ability to dual-wield, so that shouldn't be a concern). I've always found summoned daggers to be nice pet weapons as they're free and I don't have to lug them around forever. Gnoll-hide lariats are awesome pet weapons, so I use those if I have them and if I need the extra stuns, but I'm not sure whether the level 24 pets will proc them yet.<br>
<br>
If your pet wields an elemental defender, it ought to also benefit from the extra AC. However, your pet can't dual wield if it has an elemental defender in its off-hand, so give your pet a couple of weapons first to force the defender into the back slot.<br>
<br>
And yes, your pet ought to wear the summoned armor and benefit from the extra AC. If you choose to go with a heavily invested pet, though, you will want to make sure your pet lives through battle, so mem up that heal spell.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulordloralon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LordLoralon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.legion-whiterose.com/avatars/legion.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#333333>(7/9/02 4:30:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1396.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.legion-whiterose.com/avatars/legion.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet questions</span><hr size=1> On a side note, the pet will also benefit from the AC/HP bonus of our focus items. This way he may live for a couple of hits more. <p><center><a href="http://www.legion-whiterose.com"><img src="http://www.legion-whiterose.com/signatures/legionnaires/loralon.jpg"></a><br><i><b>Verba Volant, Scripta Manent</b></i></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usumlain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sumlain</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#333333>(7/10/02 4:42:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1396.topic&index=3>Reply</a> 